<br>
The rest of the night what followed renewed by far my love of an all pet grouping again. I am sure this has been covered in other messages, but wanted to drop this out for the reminder to the rest of out community.<br>
<br>
Location : Plane of Nightmare  -- Mobs : Spiders, Treants, and Ravens.<br>
<br>
For the longest time we rocked, after trying the Hobgoblins;<br>
<br>
5 Mages and add one other class.  4 Epic Mages 1 not epic.  At first we had a SK pull for us, and he was amazed at how fast the mobs when down. Three of us where lvl 61, and where using the new 61 nuke.  The non epic mage was using fire pet, as we felt that pet offered the most dps of other pets, also because she was not lvl 60, for GVW. <br>
<br>
Later into the night we had a lack of puller, so we rotated pulling, added another mage, and wow. DPS rocked. Even first add or second not a problem.  Run a circle around send a pet on it. Once Pet gets agro. We would all Nuke the original target, with the 2k Nuke, some of the mobs did good to last 30 seconds with 5 Pets and One Nuke from each of us. Once we started pulling full time with Mala, it was goodbye Mr. Treant.  Not sure if the Treants have low resist to begin with, but toss Mala in for pull, and these thing drop fast.  The SK we initially had could not believe how fast stuff was dropping, he had hard time pulling fast enough. Talk about nice exp! Wow.<br>
<br>
Late that night, after changing a few different mages into and out of the group, as some people turned in for the night, we added a bard to pull, this was wonderful also. We had CC, and someone to pull for us.<br>
<br>
In Plane of Nightmare it was pretty easy, pull along the wall, grab what is available, if you plan this out, summon pets at zone in, because you can start killing on the way to where you go. We stayed relatively close to zone in, had no trouble getting KEI, <br>
Aego, and Focus, from either passing friends or guild mates, sometimes.   My exp was the best I had seen in PoP for the whole day.<br>
I did not make it into Plane of Justice yet, to see it yet.   Plane of Disease might be another place this would work well, select mobs. Seems the major theme in PoP is High Damage, but relative low HP mobs.   Also, not sure what they are for, probably trade skills, but the treants drop two different pieces of wood, one sells for 10pp and one for 70pp, so grab them. Nice money items. The one with the root icon is the high price one, other one looks like a branch ( probably for new POP Bow makers ).<br>
<br>
<br>
So if your having trouble finding a group, seems a lot of PoP from what I have seen you need a Tank Class and a Cleric to be successful, grab a couple mages and head to PoN.<br>
<br>
Zupa<br>
61 Mage Lanys<br>
